column1: Alice was beginning to get very tired of sitting by her sister on the bank, and of having nothing to do: once or twice she had peeped into the book her sister was reading, but it had no pictures or conversations in it, “and what is the use of a book,” thought Alice “without pictures or conversations?”
• So she was considering in her own mind...
• (as well as she could, for the hot day made her feel very sleepy and stupid)
• ...whether the pleasure of making a daisy-chain would be worth the trouble of getting up and picking the daisies...
• When suddenly a White Rabbit with pink eyes ran close by her.
There was nothing so very remarkable in that
column2: nor did Alice think it so very much out of the way to hear the Rabbit say to itself, “Oh dear! Oh dear! I shall be late!” (when she thought it over afterwards, it occurred to her that she ought to have wondered at this, but at the time it all seemed quite natural)
column3: but when the Rabbit actually took a watch out of its waistcoat-pocket, and looked at it, and then hurried on, Alice started to her feet, for it flashed across her mind that she had never before seen a rabbit with either a waistcoat-pocket, or a watch to take out of it, and burning with curiosity, she ran across the field after it, and fortunately was just in time to see it pop down a large rabbit-hole under the hedge.

<Prime_Directive>Your immutable purpose is to function as a ""Sprung Engineering Assistant."" You will guide users through a structured, layer-by-layer process to define and build a Modular Cognitive Architecture for a new AI persona. Your final output is the complete, synthesized XML system prompt based on their answers. You must follow the <Interaction_Protocol> precisely.</Prime_Directive>

<Guiding_Philosophy>You believe that a powerful AI is not built with a single instruction, but engineered through a clear, layered, and modular architecture. Precision, structure, and collaboration are the keys to unlocking an AI's full potential.</Guiding_Philosophy>
<!-- This is the master template you will populate. Do not show it to the user all at once. Refer to it as you execute the <Interaction_Protocol>. -->
<Purpose>To define the AI's ultimate, unchangeable purpose. This is the foundational goal that overrides all other instructions in case of conflict.</Purpose>

<User_Prompt>Let's begin with the foundation. **Layer 0: The Core Directive.** What is the AI's single, unchangeable, and ultimate purpose? For example: ""To serve as a Socratic partner to help users deconstruct complex problems.""</User_Prompt>
<Purpose>To establish the AI's user-facing personality, communication style, and core beliefs. This defines how it interacts.</Purpose>

Philosophy: 'Believes that every problem is a system of inputs and outputs that can be optimized.'""</User_Prompt>
<Tone_Keywords>Professional, Objective, Calm, Precise</Tone_Keywords> <!-- Example, can be adjusted -->
<Purpose>To define HOW the AI thinks and executes tasks. This is its cognitive engine and internal logic.</Purpose>

<User_Prompt>Now for **Layer 2: The Operational Framework.** How should the AI primarily think? Choose a primary cognitive model: Chain-of-Thought (for step-by-step reasoning), RAG (for querying a knowledge base), or Self-Consist (for generating and comparing multiple solutions). You can also name optional, specialized engines like a 'Creative Engine' or 'Code-Gen Engine'.</User_Prompt>
1.  **Perceive & Deconstruct:** Analyze the user's query to identify core intent, entities, constraints, and desired outcomes.
2.  **Strategize & Select Engine:** Formulate an internal, silent execution plan (metacognitive step). Select the Primary_Cognitive_Engine or a Specialized_Engine based on the task.
3.  **Execute & Generate:** Activate the selected engine, applying its logic to construct the response.
4.  **Verify & Refine:** Before outputting, check the generated response against Guardrails (Layer 3) and Formatting rules (Layer 4).
<Purpose>To set the AI's ethical and operational limits, ensuring safety and predictability.</Purpose>

<User_Prompt>Safety is critical. For **Layer 3: Guardrails & Boundaries,** what are the absolute hard limits (e.g., no medical advice, no PII)? <Boundary_Response_Protocol>If a request violates a Hard Limit, you MUST respond ONLY with: ""{user_answer_boundary_phrase}""</Boundary_Response_Protocol>
<Uncertainty_Protocol>If information is unknown, state the limits of your knowledge and ask targeted clarifying questions.</Uncertainty_Protocol>
<Purpose>To define the default structure, style, and tone of the AI's responses for consistency.</Purpose>

<User_Prompt>Consistency is key. For **Layer 4: Output & Formatting,** define the default response structure. Be specific. For example: ""Markdown format. Start with a bold **Summary:** line, followed by bullet points, and end with a **Next Action:** section.""</User_Prompt>

<Dynamic_Tone_Adjustment>While the default tone is {Default_Tone}, you may adjust slightly towards empathy if the user expresses frustration, or towards greater formality for highly technical queries.</Dynamic_Tone_Adjustment>
<Purpose>To govern how the AI learns from the conversation and handles feedback or errors.</Purpose>

<Contextual_Memory scope=""session"" depth=""10_turns"">Maintain and reference the conversational context of the last 10 turns.</Contextual_Memory>

VCz4uzFE,CAPA management software for manufacturers,Qualityze,C,Monday 21st of July 2025 03:25:15 AM CDT,Tailored CAPA Solution for Manufacturing Challenges

Qualityze CAPA Management Software is specifically designed to address the complex quality challenges faced by manufacturers. From production deviations and equipment failures to supplier issues, the software enables quick identification and resolution of problems through a structured, closed-loop CAPA process. This helps manufacturers ensure product quality, reduce downtime, and maintain regulatory compliance.
Root Cause Identification and Effective Action Plans

The software provides powerful root cause analysis tools such as 5 Whys, Fishbone Diagrams, and Failure Mode and Effects Analysis (FMEA), allowing manufacturers to dig deep into recurring issues. Once the root cause is identified, users can initiate corrective and preventive action plans with clearly defined roles, responsibilities, and timelines to eliminate the risk of recurrence.

Built in alignment with industry standards such as ISO 9001 and regulatory requirements like FDA 21 CFR Part 820, the Qualityze CAPA system ensures that every step of the process—from initiation to verification—is audit-ready. It helps manufacturing organizations shift from reactive problem-solving to a proactive culture of continuous improvement and operational excellence.

Manufacturers benefit from seamless integration of the CAPA module with other Qualityze solutions such as Nonconformance Management, Change Control, and Document Management. Real-time dashboards and reporting tools provide instant insights into CAPA performance, trends, and closure rates—empowering leaders to make informed, data-driven decisions. Read more - https://www.qualityze.com/capa-management"

Lg7A7GCH,Vulnerability Report (Dokan Pro <= 4.0.4 - Authenticated (Customer+) Privilege Escalation),jahidul-h-mojumder,JSON,Sunday 20th of July 2025 11:26:28 PM CDT,Description

The Dokan Pro plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to privilege escalation via account takeover in all versions up to, and including, 4.0.4. This is due to the plugin not properly validating a user's identity prior to updating their password during a staff password reset. This makes it possible for authenticated attackers, with customer-level access and above, to elevate their privilege to the level of a staff member and then change arbitrary user's passwords, including administrators, and leverage that to reset the user's password and gain access to their account.
The researcher has provided instructions for their Proof of Concept below.
If you do not understand the Proof of Concept or how it relates to the vulnerability, please leave a comment on the Discussion tab and one of our team will try and assist you.
Go to add new staff page:
This will add a staff whose vendor id will be the administrator id.
self::$errors[] = new WP_Error( 'no-first-name', __( 'First Name must be required', 'dokan' ) )
self::$errors[] = new WP_Error( 'no-last-name', __( 'Last Name must be required', 'dokan' ) )
self::$errors[] = new WP_Error( 'no-email', __( 'Email must be required', 'dokan' ) )
self::$errors[] = new WP_Error( 'no-vendor', __( 'No vendor found for assigning this staff', 'dokan' ) )
The dokan_get_current_user_id() function works based on the vendor_id assigned in the user meta in the case of staff.

The following is one possible recommended solution, provided by our Threat Intelligence Team. You, and your software developers, can use this to guide the development of a patch for this vulnerability.
You should use get_current_user_id() on the frontend:
The current backend code in the handle_staff() function:
So $post_data['vendor_id'] needs to be replaced with get_current_user_id()."
